Catalina

Core servlet container of Tomcat.

Responsible for:

Request processing
Servlet lifecycle
Session management
6. Coyote

HTTP connector component.

Handles:

HTTP/HTTPS communication
Client connections
7. Jasper

JSP engine.

Converts:
JSP → Java Servlet

Important Directories
8. bin/

Contains startup scripts.

Examples:

startup.sh
shutdown.sh

Windows:

startup.bat
9. conf/

Configuration files.

Important files:

server.xml
web.xml
tomcat-users.xml
10. webapps/

Deployment folder.

WAR files placed here get deployed automatically.

Example:

webapps/myapp.war
11. logs/

Stores log files.

Useful for debugging.

12. temp/

Temporary runtime files.

13. work/

Compiled JSP servlet files stored here.
